      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIRST DAY (6) was unsuited to leading last time out, and did well to battle home into fourth at Wagga just over 5 weeks ago. She has been placed in her only start on this course, and with a 4.5kg weight drop, she is good enough to take this out. STAR BLAZER (1) had an excuse when finishing fifth in a 7-horse field at Wagga 6-days go, and the quick backup should not bother him being so deep into his prep. He benefits from a 3kg claim and can make amends. Each way. DEVIL RIDER (3) has been very disappointing in heavy ground in his last 2 starts, and if he can find a firmer surface here, then a form reversal would be no surprise at all. CAYMAN ISLAND (7) has found it hard to win another race, and he has needed time to mature. He steps up to this trip for the first time, and he has sound each-way claims. BEACHED AS BRO (9) has been thereabouts in 2 starts since posting an overdue maiden win at Wagga-Riverside. He drops 5kg from his last start, and won't be far away in this. Include.",
